    <div class="h-mega">ECOSYSTEM</div>
    <h1 class="h-title">HomeTest is a small core surrounded by a larger ecosystem.</h1>
    <div class="h-subtitle">Five relationships HomeTest holds with the world around it.</div>
  <section style="padding:40px 60px 48px;background:#fff;border-top:1px solid #ebeef1;border-bottom:1px solid #ebeef1;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px;">
      <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:#7E8B97;text-transform:uppercase;">How the model travels into the world</div>
      <div style="flex:1;height:1px;background:#ebeef1;"></div>
    </div>
    <h2 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:900;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.6px;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:12px;">Routes to scale.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:14.5px;color:#4C6272;line-height:1.7;max-width:880px;margin-bottom:24px;">HomeTest is a small core surrounded by a larger ecosystem. Scale travels through that ecosystem in three routes. Each carries different friction, different unit economics, and a different sales conversation. The framework supports all three; the centre&apos;s prioritisation choice is which route to lean on first.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;">
      <div style="background:#F4F8FC;border:1px solid #d6e2ef;border-left:5px solid #005EB8;border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.4px;color:#005EB8;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Route 1 &middot; Greenfield</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:10px;">A new service stood up from scratch.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:#4C6272;line-height:1.65;">A commissioner commissions home testing for a cohort that does not currently have a digital pathway. The platform brokers the supplier and the IG; the commissioner builds the service. <strong>Highest control, slowest cycle, most upfront work.</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#FFF9EC;border:1px solid #F0DCA0;border-left:5px solid #C9A227;border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.4px;color:#9A6700;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Route 2 &middot; Brownfield switch</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:10px;">An existing service shifts venue from clinic to home.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:#4C6272;line-height:1.65;">An acute trust&apos;s phlebotomy clinic, a GP practice&apos;s routine monitoring slot, an LA-commissioned testing service: existing demand, existing budget, existing pathway. The home pathway substitutes the venue. <strong>Fastest scale, hardest sales conversation</strong> &mdash; the substitution has to be earned at the local level.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#F4FAF7;border:1px solid #cfe1d8;border-left:5px solid #006747;border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.4px;color:#1F4435;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Route 3 &middot; Programme-led</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:10px;">A national programme adopts the configuration into its rollout.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:#4C6272;line-height:1.65;">NHS Online, screening programmes, NHS Health Check: a national programme picks up the configuration and carries it into the cohort it already serves. The platform provides the rails; the programme provides the demand and the route to patient. <strong>Least friction; bounded to programmes that exist.</strong></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

    <p class="h-intro">The HomeTest BAU team is small because most operating mass sits outside it. The team <strong>builds, runs and stewards</strong> a specific core. Almost everything else is <strong>consumed</strong> from NHS infrastructure, <strong>regulated by</strong> an external body, <strong>contracted</strong> commercially, or <strong>served</strong> as the output. Being an intelligent client across the four outer categories is itself a substantial job: holding suppliers to SLA, holding consumed services to interfaces, holding regulators to timelines.</p>
  </div>

